details.address: 13717 E Independence Blvd, Indian Trail, NC 28079
details.description:
At Sugar Creek Coffee Roasters, we specialize in hand crafted, small batch, artisan roasted coffee. We don't roast your coffee beans until you place an order, so you can be assured the freshest roasted coffee is delivered to your door.
​
Located inside Sweet Union Brewing in Indian Trail, North Carolina, we're proud to support the local economy, as well as ship freshly roasted beans across the United States. We have a growing list of partnerships, including breweries and coffee shops, as well as several non-profit organizations that benefit from our support.

reviews_data.review_text: I’m not sure where to start with this coffee. So delicious!  I cannot recommend it enough. I tried it on a men’s ski trip to Colorado.  We drank “Weight in Gold” in a drip coffee pot all week. I had a hard time stopping at 2 cups. Afterwards I ordered a few different bags and blends. I tried “Nail on the Head” this morning in my aero press. Wonderful!  Hats off to the coffee scientists at Sugar Creek who geniusly figured out all these perfect blends.  Chris Berger is the best!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the kind words and review. So glad you are enjoying the coffee!

reviews_data.review_text:
My wife and I have been ordering from Sugar Creek Coffee Roasters for about 6 months  and our experience has been nothing short of fantastic.

We moved to Charlotte from Sydney, Australia about a year ago and were really having a tough time finding a roaster that could match the quality of espresso beans we were used to
in Australia. Long story short, we signed up for the 4-bag monthly subscription with Sugar Creek a few months ago and have been loving every new bag of beans.

The customer service is is exceptional. Prompt, polite, and very accommodating. Chris is a real legend.

The beans are roasted the day before they send them out to you, so you get an amazingly fresh batch every time. This level of freshness makes for unbelievable crema when you're pulling your morning shot of espresso.

If you're an espresso lover, I definitely recommend that you place an order with Sugar Creek Coffee Roasters.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the kind review! We greatly appreciate amazing customers like you!

reviews_data.review_text: This is the only coffee we use in our expresso machine. The coffee is the best I have ever tasted anywhere! Chris is such a nice person to do business with! They only roast the coffee after you’ve placed your order and they deliver to my house since I’m in the 10 mi radius. Our family recommends them to everyone wanting good coffee, love them! 😍
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the very kind words! We greatly appreciate you!

reviews_data.review_text: Ordered some fresh beans and was not disappointed. Some of the best coffee I've ever tasted. Highly recommend this place!

reviews_data.review_text: I ordered online and the crema i got from my espresso pour was amazing! And i really appreciate the extra bag i cant wait to try it :) i really think this is the roasters i stick with!

reviews_data.review_text:
DISCLAIMER: Only tried the coffee.

Cute hipster brewer, the beer looks tasty. Popular with the 30-50s crowd, so if you're looking for friends I'm sure Friday nights here are great.

Alternitavely, I'm not sure why they call their nitro cold brew with sweeteners "lattes." If you're looking for coffee I can't recommend this place.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Spencer, they are called cold brew lattes since they are made with cold brewed coffee concentrate and milk — which is the actual definition of a latte. Straight cold brew is not a latte (not sure if this is what you had). Also, we are primarily a coffee ROASTER, as our name implies, that serves some products for those that can’t or don’t drink beer in the brewery. We roast for local coffee shops, where you can get your hot latte, and we roast for people to make coffee at home…which is why we don’t advertise or say or claim we are a full blown coffee shop.

reviews_data.review_text: Huge fan of this place. I make and drink espresso, and most roasters local to the Charlotte area sell extremely light roasts only. Sugar creek offers a great range, and their medium/dark roasts are as well thought out as their lights, and take flavor profile seriously. Huge fan of their weight in gold roast.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the kind words, David! Really appreciate you noticing the care we take in our specialty blends, and yes, while we love light roasts, we certainly have a special place for medium and darker roasts!

reviews_data.review_text:
Stopped by just because it popped up on Google when I searched for coffee. This place is unique with food and a bar as well as coffee. Loved their coffee selections though and tried their unique Shandy flavor which was a mix of lemonade and coffee.

It’s definitely an acquired taste as my wife hated it but I found it to be delightful and filled with wonder. A taste like nothing you’ve had before so worth finding out if you’re a fan or not.

Service was epic too and I got to sample the Shandy before purchasing. Happy they were so kind and helpful in me trying something new! Highly recommend exploring this place.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the very kind words, Les! And so glad you liked the shandy, our take on a coffee Arnold Palmer!

reviews_data.review_text: Chris and his team did a phenomenal job providing coffee service to myself and my bridal party on the morning of our wedding. They took great care of us and the coffee was absolutely delicious. Chris was a pleasure to work with and would highly recommend them for any event or for a great cup of coffee!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much, Chelsea! It was a pleasure and honor to be able to serve you on your special day. We appreciate the very kind note!

reviews_data.review_text: Love their coffee and the staff is super friendly. Only reason I’m giving 4 stars is they have late opening hours, so I’m unable to stop and get my coffee when I need it. I’ve been out for a while and getting there mid afternoon when they open isn’t too convenient.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Matt, thanks for the comment and review. As you may see in our name, we are a first and foremost a coffee roastery — which means we are a supplier of coffee products to customers and actual coffee shops. We don’t advertise ourselves as a coffee shop, since doing so would be “biting the hand that feeds us” as you can imagine. Once we do that, we become competitors to the very places we supply, so I’m sure you can see how that wouldn’t work with our current business model. The products we do sell at the roastery are those that are on tap at the brewery and our kcups. That’s why we have the same hours as the brewery.

reviews_data.review_text:
UPDATE: I have to update my review because they keep getting better and better.  I make a lot of at home espresso based drinks.  The lighter roast, Nail On The Head is super well balanced, their espresso roast Weight in Gold is smooth without being too harsh, and their darker roast, Midnight Oil makes a fantastic Italian style espresso...bolder but still not harsh.  Roasting is always within a day or two, and the stuff is on my doorstep within a few days of ordering.  Can't say enough good about them.
ORIGINAL POST:
The coffee is very good.  I order whole bean Weight in Gold Espresso blend and it is always roasted fresh within a day or so.   Flavor is great for straight espresso or milk based drinks.  Hard to beat the service from these folks.  Ordering two bags or more and you can have free delivery within a 10 mile radius.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much! Greatly appreciate your very kind review and being a great customer!

reviews_data.review_text: Excellent coffee and great service! And you can change gears quick to the beer side too since it's together with Sweet Union Brewing.

reviews_data.review_text: I ordered based on a recommendation on Next Door by my neighbor, who I know loves her coffee. This coffee is some of the best I've tasted in a long time. It made me pull out the old coffee maker and ditch the Keurig too, so win win. I posted on my personal FB page how pleased I was. It was also delivered to me within hours of my placing the order. Their customer service is incredible and I cannot wait to share with my coffee friends once we are released from shelter at home order. I have always liked the idea of supporting local, but there are less opportunities during a busy life to really do so. This slow down gave me the time to try something different and be so thrilled with the product, that I will be supporting a local business for the foreseeable future.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the incredibly kind words! We love roasting for the local community and supporting great organizations around us. Please let us know if there is anything we can ever do for you!

reviews_data.review_text: Well, what can I say other than the name fits the bean! This coffee once brewed is nice, full of flavor,  and smooth. My hubby has been drinking their coffee over the years and it was so fun to visit the space where they roast. Bonus,  they share a space with the Sweet Union Brewing company so when you go pick up your coffee, you might as well try some local craft beer on draft. They have used Sugar Creek coffee in some of their beers which is pretty cool. Another thing that made it fun is you can watch the roasting process firsthand and see on the screen what is happening to the beans.  I found this mesmerizing...but that might be just me. My hubby and I have used this coffee as a go to gift for those "you never know what to give" as a "thank you happy day" present because what is there not to love? So anyway,  I totally recommend you try them out if you are looking for a "craft" fresh roast coffee.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the thoughtful and kind words! We’re so glad you love fresh roasted coffee as much as we do! ☕️

reviews_data.review_text: We get their monthly subscription!! Best coffee !! Hands down !! They roast it to our exact specifications, and it is delivered right to our door!! We like being able to try new coffee every month !! I would definitely recommend this brand to friends and family

reviews_data.review_text: Found out about Sugar Creek Coffee Roasters through a friend who works at a coffee shop in Cornelius. Wow! This recommendation did not disappoint. I was almost overwhelmed with the variety of roasts they offer for a local business. I am definitely going to be purchasing some beans as future gifts for friends and family. Thank you!!!

reviews_data.review_text: I ordered some coffee from Sugar Creek to give as holiday gifts to my clients. Though I live in Oklahoma, far from Matthews, NC, the coffee arrived in just a few days, just in time to hand out to my clients, and came in nicely branded packaging. Upon opening, not only was I enveloped with an amazing aroma that only comes with fresh roasted coffee, there was also a hand-written note from Sugar Creek's owner expressing appreciation for my business. So classy! I kept a bag of perfectly roasted Ethiopian Guji for myself and enjoyed its crazy notes of strawberry. My clients enjoyed the coffee too, one client describing the Sumatra as smooth and rich, and another described the Holiday Blend as "the most amazing cup of 'reason to wake up' ever!" You can't get any better than that! The purchase process, communication and product made for simple but great experience. I will definitely be ordering again.

reviews_data.review_text: Sugar Creek Coffee is the freshest small batch roasted coffee in the Matthews-Trail area. Each type of bean is researched to give the final roasted beans the best flavor. reviews_data.review_text:
Incredible coffee roasted to perfection.

Before I tried SCCR coffee, I used to doubt all of the "super taster" descriptions--I never detected things like "hints of  chocolate and molasses". I was also a "lots of sugar, lots of cream" guy even with what I used to consider to be good coffee. SCCR coffee tastes great black, especially when cold-brewed.

Coffee bean hierarchy:
Sugar Creek Coffee Roasters > Other artisanal roasters > Starbucks > Royal Cup

It's worth a few extra bucks to start the day right.

raw_data.name: Sugar Creek Coffee Roasters
raw_data.full_address: 13717 E Independence Blvd, Indian Trail, NC 28079
raw_data.description:
At Sugar Creek Coffee Roasters, we specialize in hand crafted, small batch, artisan roasted coffee. We don't roast your coffee beans until you place an order, so you can be assured the freshest roasted coffee is delivered to your door.
​
Located inside Sweet Union Brewing in Indian Trail, North Carolina, we're proud to support the local economy, as well as ship freshly roasted beans across the United States. We have a growing list of partnerships, including breweries and coffee shops, as well as several non-profit organizations that benefit from our support.

reviews_data.review_text: I’m not sure where to start with this coffee. So delicious!  I cannot recommend it enough. I tried it on a men’s ski trip to Colorado. reviews_data.review_text:
My wife and I have been ordering from Sugar Creek Coffee Roasters for about 6 months  and our experience has been nothing short of fantastic.

We moved to Charlotte from Sydney, Australia about a year ago and were really having a tough time finding a roaster that could match the quality of espresso beans we were used to
in Australia. Long story short, we signed up for the 4-bag monthly subscription with Sugar Creek a few months ago and have been loving every new bag of beans.

The customer service is is exceptional. Prompt, polite, and very accommodating. Chris is a real legend.

The beans are roasted the day before they send them out to you, so you get an amazingly fresh batch every time. This level of freshness makes for unbelievable crema when you're pulling your morning shot of espresso.

If you're an espresso lover, I definitely recommend that you place an order with Sugar Creek Coffee Roasters.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the kind review! We greatly appreciate amazing customers like you!

reviews_data.review_text: This is the only coffee we use in our expresso machine. The coffee is the best I have ever tasted anywhere! Chris is such a nice person to do business with! reviews_data.review_text:
DISCLAIMER: Only tried the coffee.

Cute hipster brewer, the beer looks tasty. Popular with the 30-50s crowd, so if you're looking for friends I'm sure Friday nights here are great.

Alternitavely, I'm not sure why they call their nitro cold brew with sweeteners "lattes." If you're looking for coffee I can't recommend this place.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Spencer, they are called cold brew lattes since they are made with cold brewed coffee concentrate and milk — which is the actual definition of a latte. Straight cold brew is not a latte (not sure if this is what you had). Also, we are primarily a coffee ROASTER, as our name implies, that serves some products for those that can’t or don’t drink beer in the brewery. We roast for local coffee shops, where you can get your hot latte, and we roast for people to make coffee at home…which is why we don’t advertise or say or claim we are a full blown coffee shop.

reviews_data.review_text: Huge fan of this place. I make and drink espresso, and most roasters local to the Charlotte area sell extremely light roasts only. Sugar creek offers a great range, and their medium/dark roasts are as well thought out as their lights, and take flavor profile seriously. Huge fan of their weight in gold roast.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the kind words, David! Really appreciate you noticing the care we take in our specialty blends, and yes, while we love light roasts, we certainly have a special place for medium and darker roasts!

reviews_data.review_text:
Stopped by just because it popped up on Google when I searched for coffee. This place is unique with food and a bar as well as coffee. Loved their coffee selections though and tried their unique Shandy flavor which was a mix of lemonade and coffee.

It’s definitely an acquired taste as my wife hated it but I found it to be delightful and filled with wonder. A taste like nothing you’ve had before so worth finding out if you’re a fan or not.

Service was epic too and I got to sample the Shandy before purchasing. Happy they were so kind and helpful in me trying something new! Highly recommend exploring this place.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the very kind words, Les! And so glad you liked the shandy, our take on a coffee Arnold Palmer!

reviews_data.review_text: Chris and his team did a phenomenal job providing coffee service to myself and my bridal party on the morning of our wedding. They took great care of us and the coffee was absolutely delicious. Chris was a pleasure to work with and would highly recommend them for any event or for a great cup of coffee!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much, Chelsea! It was a pleasure and honor to be able to serve you on your special day. We appreciate the very kind note!

reviews_data.review_text: Love their coffee and the staff is super friendly. Only reason I’m giving 4 stars is they have late opening hours, so I’m unable to stop and get my coffee when I need it. I’ve been out for a while and getting there mid afternoon when they open isn’t too convenient.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Matt, thanks for the comment and review. As you may see in our name, we are a first and foremost a coffee roastery — which means we are a supplier of coffee products to customers and actual coffee shops. We don’t advertise ourselves as a coffee shop, since doing so would be “biting the hand that feeds us” as you can imagine. Once we do that, we become competitors to the very places we supply, so I’m sure you can see how that wouldn’t work with our current business model. The products we do sell at the roastery are those that are on tap at the brewery and our kcups. That’s why we have the same hours as the brewery.

reviews_data.review_text:
UPDATE: I have to update my review because they keep getting better and better.  I make a lot of at home espresso based drinks.  The lighter roast, Nail On The Head is super well balanced, their espresso roast Weight in Gold is smooth without being too harsh, and their darker roast, Midnight Oil makes a fantastic Italian style espresso...bolder but still not harsh.  Roasting is always within a day or two, and the stuff is on my doorstep within a few days of ordering.  Can't say enough good about them.

The coffee is very good.  I order whole bean Weight in Gold Espresso blend and it is always roasted fresh within a day or so.   Flavor is great for straight espresso or milk based drinks.  Hard to beat the service from these folks.  Ordering two bags or more and you can have free delivery within a 10 mile radius.
